{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnapshotManager","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SnapshotManager"},{"text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the VM’s disk image (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"text":") and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"auxiliary.bin"},{"text":"), stored in a named subdirectory under the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SavedStates\/"},{"text":" directory.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How Snapshots Work","anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must be stopped"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" before saving or restoring.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the snapshot copies.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Snapshot Directory Layout","anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Example","anchor":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","","\/\/ Save a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.save(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ List snapshots","let snapshots = try SnapshotManager.list(bundle: bundle)","for snap in snapshots {","    print(\"\\(snap.label): \\(snap.sizeInBytes) bytes\")","}","","\/\/ Restore a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.restore(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ Delete a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.delete(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")"]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Enumeration","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"symbolKind":"enum","title":"SnapshotManager","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnapshotManager","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit15SnapshotManagerO"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Snapshots","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/Spooktacul